verbose_text: HA-SLNs / PTX binding efficiency was weaker in the presence of antibody and hyaluronic acid than that in its absence, which suggested that anti-CD44 antibodies and hyaluronic acid inhibited the cell association of HA-SLNs / PTX.
evidence: anti-CD44 antibodies and hyaluronic acid inhibited the cell association of HA-SLNs/PTX
